info.name: Bichard 7 Audit Logging API
info.description:
# Overview
This RESTful API is for accessing everything relating to Audit Log records. These come from messages from an external system, and also comprise of events emitted from the internal Bichard7 system. The API is built as an AWS API Gateway and backed by individual AWS Lambda Functions to serve each individual endpoint.

# Authentication
This is a private API and it doesn't require authentication. This API can only be accessed within the VPC.

query.description: Optional - Used for pagination. Setting this query parameter will return the next 10 records from this message ID

request.description:
This API endpoint returns the last 10 audit log records ordered by `receivedDate` descending. This endpoint also supports pagination by passing the last message ID which returns the next 10 records.

`lastMessageId` query parameter is optional and only used for pagination.

response.name: Get last 10 messages

request.description:
This API endpoint is for retrying a failed audit log record.

A failed audit log record is a record that:
- has `Error` status, and
- its most recent event status is `Error`, and
- its most recent event has `S3Path` and `eventSourceQueueName` fields set.

Calling this API endpoint will retrieve the event data from S3 and pushes it to the queue to be processed by Bichard. The status of the audit log record will then become `Retrying`.
